<br>
Why must there always be an ill mannered ass in the crowd?  Let me make myself more clear.  The group I pointed out is the most efficient group I'VE been in in PoP.  The tank was actually a Pally not a warrior.  That has been MY experience.  <br>
<br>
The point I was trying to make is that we should be in higher demand and sought out first before any other damage class.  We are in more demand but still people don't realize how well we stack.  I was not allowed into a group because they already had a wizard and wanted more melee damage.  They didn't think i'd stack well enough or could sustain as high a damage as a rogue or another monk.  Same thing happened to me at EXE Trial group.  Leader wanted 3 rogues as the damage dealer and no casters.  The word is getting out but not totally out yet.<br>
<br>
And yes I have done some very untraditional groups that were great.  Had Me (61 mage), Ranger (EQ/AM3), DC Enchanter, 56 druid (so didn't even have the new healing spell), Bard, and 60 mage.  We let DC pet tank the slowed mob then sent in pets and let ranger pull and smack with bow.  We did just fine, but it was not nearly as powerful as the group with DC enchanter, cleric, pally, and 3 mages.<br>
<br>
It just so happens to be that the core of the group that is mention and that is &quot;traditional&quot; happens to be very effective, especially with mobs that mash for 400.  I would argue though that the mage in its current form is the best exp damage dealer now, and stacks better than any other class for what it does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=omegasyphon>omegasyphon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 593<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/02 9:44:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=405.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   comment</span><hr size=1> i hate that crap to, knowbody wants to start a groop if u have no warrior  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dlaren4444>dlaren4444</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/02 9:52:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=405.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: i guess you never where in a all pet group? :)</span><hr size=1>  Thinking outside the box means every Xp grind does not have to have the traditional character classes in it. I was in a HoH group the other nite that was this:<br>
