<br>
Shamans have never had trouble getting groups, and they won't be hurt by this either. I can see this slightly helping beastlords, since they might be better in all pet groups than a shaman (lower slow, but a shaman can't do the damage of a BL pet without getting agro).<br>
<br>
I think POP is screwed up, but really my biggest issue at the moment isn't needing to find a group (which I think is within Verant's right to change), but the fact that I should be banking my epic + toxiferous axe combo for a 2hs and a haste belt, since dual wield and 2hs are so massively unbalanced right now. (i.e. 34dmg 23dly 2hs dropping off same mob as a 15/19 1hs, and the 2hs has a lower recommended level) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andurravenblade>Andur Ravenblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/02 2:52:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=405.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Wow...</span><hr size=1> ...some of you just haven't been reading. It's about the slow, and duh a group with a SK and no healer is gonna gimp fast. The way it works and ill go step by step.<br>
<br>
Step 1.<br>
<br>
Pick your slower.<br>
<br>
Step 2.<br>
<br>
Pick your healer.<br>
<br>
Step 3.<br>
<br>
Pick your tank.<br>
<br>
Step 4.<br>
<br>
Pick everyone else.<br>
<br>
So for instance, if you have a shaman for step 1. Your next step is easier because you can skip getting a healer and use the shaman or easily stick a druid or cleric in if wanted. Then you move to step 3, with a shaman slowing just about anything can tank, what you need to decide at this point is whether it's going to be a pet tanking group or not. Step 4, if you ended up with pets as tanks you don't add a rogue as it won't have access to it's back (Monks and Rangers would tank fine against a shaman slowed mob). Otherwise any other class can fit Step 4.<br>
<br>
Group make up could end up being like this...<br>
<br>
Shaman Mage Necro Beastlord Bard Ranger<br>
<br>
<br>
or like this<br>
<br>
Shaman Warrior Rogue Mage Chanter Druid<br>
<br>
or like this<br>
<br>
Shaman Cleric Paladin Monk Monk Wizard<br>
<br>
All of these groups will gain exp as fast as the other (with a little variance for dps but we are talking very minimal differences unless your talking 24 hour + stints of exp gaining).<br>
<br>
Here is an example of creating a group without a Shaman (in case some people still aren't getting it). For this instance we will use a Beastlord as slower (this assumes no enchanter/shaman available).<br>
<br>
So group could end up like this...<br>
<br>
Beastlord Mage Mage Wizard Wizard Bard<br>
<br>
or this<br>
<br>
Beastlord Cleric Warrior Paladin Monk Necro<br>
<br>
or this<br>
<br>
Beastlord Ranger Druid Druid Shadow Knight Rogue<br>
<br>
You can do alot of switching around in the groups, but you have to balance it a bit differently mostly based on the slower, and then again if it's an all pet group (at which point less healing can be necessary).<br>
<br>
