<br>
Not neccesarily.  You could have an enchanter, beastlord, bard and shaman, with say, a tank and a mage.  Now that group would rock, don't you agree?  But you have all the slowing classes there.<br>
<br>
2 beastlords?  We have enough damage, we stack.  but gotta find two beastlords.<br>
2 shamans? Stack, one buffs, one debuffs, or one goes damage.<br>
2 bards?  Again, buff/debuff or damage.  But gotta find two GOOD bards.<br>
Two enchanters, well yeah, chanters don't really compliment each other that much.<br>
<br>
Some combinations won't work, but most slowing classes have enough utility to not be invalidated by another slower present.<br>
<br>
